is S  Riddick s World War II album  They were taken during 1943 1944 on New Hebrides and Bougainville  Solomon Islands  Willis S  Riddick  Jr  graduated from VMI in 1939 with a B  S  degree in Chemistry  He entered the U  S  Army in July 1940 and served until his retirement in 1967  rising to the rank of Colonel  A decorated veteran of 33 months of overseas duty during World War II  he served with Battery  A  6th Field Artillery Battalion  in the Pacific Theater  The unit was at New Hebrides  Guadalcanal  Bougainville  and the Philippines  Col  Riddick died in 1999  VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu 